article.headline: IUPUI 68, UMKC 62
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- George Hill had 13 of his game-high 21 points in the second half Thursday to lead IUPUI to a 68-62 Mid-Continent Conference victory over Missouri-Kansas City. It was the fourth-straight conference win for the Jaguars (9-6, 4-0 MCC), and ended a three-game winning streak for UMKC. The Kangaroos (7-8, 4-2) led 39-35 at halftime, but an 8-0 IUPUI run midway through the second half tied the game at 50-50. The Jaguars took a 56-54 lead at the 8:34 mark and didn't trail the rest of the way. Brandon Cole and David Barlow each had 14 points for IUPUI, which hit 15 of 17 free throws. Quinton Day and Brent Stephens scored 13 points each to lead the Kangaroos. Day also had nine rebounds and eight assists.
